<p>Mo ḥammad-Maʿṣum b. Ḵvājagi Eṣfahāni, <em>Ḵolāṣat al-siar: tāriḵ-e ruzgār-e &Scaron;āh Ṣafi Ṣafawi</em>, ed. Iraj Af&scaron;ār, Tehran, 1989; tr. Gerhard Rettelbach as <em>Ḫulasat al-siyar: der Iran unter Schah Safi (1629-1642)</em>, Beitr&auml;ge zur Kenntnis S&uuml;dosteuropas und des Nahen Orients 29, Munich, 1978.</p>
<p>Moḥammad Mofid Mostawfi Bāfqi, <em>Jāmeʿ-e mofidi</em>, facs. ed. Iraj Af&scaron;ār, 3 vols., Tehran, 1961-64.</p>
<p>Aṣḡar Montaẓer-e Ṣāḥeb, ed., <em>ʿĀlamārā-ye &Scaron;āh Esmāʿil</em>, Tehran, 1970. Yad-Allāh &Scaron;okri, ed., <em>ʿĀlamārā-ye Ṣafawi</em>, Tehran, 1971.</p>
<p>Mir Moḥammad-Saʿid Mo&scaron;iri Bardasiri, <em>Taḏkera-ye safawi-e Kermān</em>, ed. Moḥammad-Ebrāhim Bāstāni Pārizi, Tehran, 1990.</p>
<p>Allāh-Detā Możṭar, facs. ed., <em>Jahāngo&scaron;ā-ye Ḵāqān</em>, Islamabad, 1984.</p>
<p>Moḥammad-Ebrāhim b. Zayn-al-ʿĀbedin Naṣiri, <em>Dastur-e &scaron;ahri-ārān: sālhā-ye 1110-1105 h. q., pād&scaron;āhi-e &Scaron;āh Solṭān Ḥosayn Ṣafawi</em>, ed. Moḥammad-Nāder Naṣiri Moqaddam, Tehran, 1994.</p>
<p>Shaikh Ḥosayn Pirzāda Zāhedi, <em>Selselat al-nasab-e Ṣafawiya</em>, ed. Kāẓemzāda Irān&scaron;ahr, Berlin, 1924.</p>
<p>Qāżi Aḥmad Ḡaffāri Qazvini, <em>Tāriḵ-e ja-hānārā</em>, ed. Ḥasan Narāqi, Tehran, 1963.</p>
<p>Qāżi Aḥmad Qomi, <em>Ḵolāṣat al-tawāriḵ</em>, ed. Eḥsān E&scaron;rāqi, 2 vols., Tehran, 1984; ed. and tr. Hans M&uuml;ller as <em>Die Chronik Ḫulāṣat at-tawāriḫ des Qāżi Aḥmad Qumī: Der Abschnitt &uuml;ber Schah ʿAbbās I</em>, Wiesbaden, 1964; ed. and tr. Erika Glassen as <em>Die fr&uuml;hen Safawiden nach Qāzi Aḥmad Qumi</em>, Islamkundliche Untersuchungen 5, Freiburg, 1970. Mirzā Samiʿā, <em>Taḏkerat al-moluk</em>, facs. ed. and tr. Vladmir Minorsky as <em>Tadhkirat al-muluk</em>, London, 1943.</p>
<p>Siāqi Neẓām, <em>Fotuḥāt-e homāyun</em>, facs. ed. ʿAbbās Zaryāb Ḵoʾi, <em>Barrasihā-ye tāriḵi</em> 8/1-2, 1973, pp. 207-78; ed. C. Adle, Ph.D. diss., Paris, 1976.</p>
<p>Waliqoli b. Dāwudqoli &Scaron;āmlu, <em>Qesās al-ḵāqāni</em>, 2 vols., ed. Ḥasan Sādāt-e Nāṣeri, Tehran, 1992-95.</p>
<p>Shah Ṭahmāsb Ṣafawi, <em>Taḏkera-ye &Scaron;āh Ṭahmāsb</em>, ed. ʿAbd-al-&Scaron;akur, Berlin, 1924; ed. Paul Horn, in <em>ZDMG </em>44, 1890, pp. 563-649; 45, 1891, pp. 245-91.</p>
<p>Amir Yaḥyā Ḥosayni Qazvini, <em>Lobb al- tawāriḵ</em>, ed. Sayyed Jalāl Ṭehrāni, Tehran, 1937.</p>
<p>Studies. A. Aṣḡar, <em>Tāriḵ-nevisi-e fārsi dar Hend o Pākestān: Timuriān-e bozorg az Bābor tā Awrangzēb, 932-1118 h.q.</em>, Lahore, 1985.</p>
<p>Jean Aubin, &ldquo;Chroniques persanes et Relations italiennes: Notes sur les Sources narratives du Regne de &Scaron;&acirc;h Esm&acirc;ʿil Ier,&rdquo; <em>Studia Iranica</em> 24/2, 1995, pp. 247-59.</p>
<p>M. Bastani Parizi (Bāstāni Pārizi), &ldquo;Moḥammad Ebrāhim, copiste d&rsquo;une histoire des seldjoukides et sa famille sur Kermān (xvi-xvii si&egrave;cle),&rdquo;<em> Studia Iranica</em> 16/1, 1987, pp. 131&mdash;35.</p>
<p>H. Beveridge and J. T. P. De Bruijn, &ldquo;Khʷāndamīr,&rdquo; in <em>EI</em>2 IV, pp. 1020-22.</p>
<p>Edward G. Browne, &ldquo;Note on an Apparently Unique Manuscript History of the Safawi Dynasty of Persia,&rdquo; <em>JRAS</em>, 1921, pp. 395-418.</p>
<p>Jean Calmard, &ldquo;Notes sur des historiographes de l&rsquo;&eacute;poque Safavide,&rdquo; <em>Studia Iranica</em> 16/1, 1987, pp. 123-24.</p>
<p>S. F. Dale, &ldquo;The Legacy of the Timurids,&rdquo; <em>JRAS</em> 8, 1998, pp. 43-58.</p>
<p>Martin B. Dickson, &ldquo;Sh&agrave;h Ṭahm&agrave;sb and the Uzbeks: The Duel for Khur&agrave;s&agrave;n with &lsquo;Ubayd Kh&agrave;n, 930-946/1524-1540,&rdquo; Ph.D. diss., Princeton University, 1958.</p>
<p>E. Echraqi, &ldquo;Le Khol&acirc;sat al-Taw&acirc;rikh de Q&acirc;zi Ahmad connu soues le nom de Mir Monshi,&rdquo; <em>Studia Iranica</em> 4/1, 1975, pp. 73-89.</p>
<p>M. Farhad, &ldquo;The Art of Muʿin Musavvir: A Mirror of His Times,&rdquo; in Sheila R. Canby, ed.,<em> Persian Masters: Five Centuries of Painting</em>, Bombay, 1990.</p>
<p>Masahi Haneda, &ldquo;La famille Huzani d&rsquo;Isfahan (15e-17e si&egrave;cles),&rdquo; <em>Studia Iranica</em> 18, 1989, pp. 77-92.</p>
<p>A. Jacobs, &ldquo;Sunni and Shiʿi Perceptions, Boundaries and Affiliations in Late Timurid and Early Safawid Persia: An Examination of Historical and Quasi-Historical Narratives,&rdquo; Ph.D. diss., University of London, 1999.</p>
<p>A. K. S. Lambton, &ldquo;Taʾrīkh 2. In Persian,&rdquo; in <em>EI</em>2 X, pp. 286-90.</p>
<p>Robert D. McChesney, &ldquo;A Note on Iskandar Beg&rsquo;s Chronology,&rdquo; <em>Journal of Near Eastern Studies</em> 39, 1980, pp. 53-63.</p>
<p>Charles Melville, &ldquo;From Qars to Qandahar: The Itineraries of Shah ʿAbbas I (995-1038 /1587-1629),&rdquo; in Jean Calmard, ed.,<em> Etudes Safavides</em>, Paris and Tehran, 1993, pp. 195-224.</p>
<p>Idem, &ldquo;Shah ʿAbbas and the Pilgrimage to Mashhad,&rdquo; in idem, ed., <em>Safavid Persia: The History and Politics of an Islamic Society</em>, London, 1996, pp. 191-229.</p>
<p>Idem, &ldquo;A Lost Source for the Reign of Shah ʿAbbas: The <em>Afżal al-tawārīkh</em> of Fazli Khuzāni Isfahani,&rdquo; <em>Iranian Studies</em> 31, 1998, pp. 263-65.</p>
<p>Idem, &ldquo;New Light on the Reign of Shah ʿAbbas: Volume III of the <em>Afḍal al-tawārikh</em>,&rdquo; forthcoming. A. H. Morton, &ldquo;The Date and Attribution of the <em>Ross Anonymous</em>: Notes on a Persian History of Shah Ismaʿil I,&rdquo; in Charles Melville, ed.,<em> Pembroke Papers</em> I: <em>Persian and Islamic Studies in Honour of P. W. Avery</em>, Cambridge, 1990, pp. 179-212.</p>
<p>Idem, &ldquo;The Early Years of Shah Ismaʿil in the <em>Afżal al-tavārikh</em> and Elsewhere,&rdquo; in Charles Melville, ed.,<em> Safavid Persia: The History and Politics of an Islamic Society</em>, London, 1996, pp. 27-51.</p>
<p>Ali Asghar Mossadegh, &ldquo;La Famille Monajjem Yazdi,&rdquo; <em>Studia Iranica</em> 16/1, 1987, pp. 123-29.</p>
<p>Sholeh A. Quinn, <em>Historical Writing during the Reign of Shah ʿAbbas I</em>, Salt Lake City, 2000.</p>
<p>Idem, &ldquo;Rewriting Niʿmatullahi History in Safavid Chronicles,&rdquo; in Leonard Lewisohn and D. Morgan, eds, <em>Late Classical Persianate Sufism (1501-1750)</em>, Oxford, 1999.</p>
<p>Giorgio Rota, &ldquo;Three Little-Known Persian Sources of the Seventeenth Century,&rdquo; <em>Iranian Studies</em> 31/2, 1998, pp. 159-76.</p>
<p>Roger Savory, &ldquo;&lsquo;Very Dull and Arduous Reading&rsquo;: A Reappraisal of the History of Shah ʿAbbas the Great by Iskandar Beg Munshi,&rdquo; <em>Hamdard Islamicus</em> 111, 1980, pp. 19-37.</p>
<p>Maria Szuppe, <em>Entre Timourides, Uzbeks et Safavides: questions d&rsquo;histoire politique et sociale de H&eacute;rat dans la premi&egrave;re moiti&eacute; du XVIe si&egrave;cle</em>, Studia Iranica, Cahier 12, Paris, 1992.</p>
<p>Idem, &ldquo;L&rsquo;&eacute;volution de l&rsquo;image de Timour et des Timourides dans l&rsquo;historiographie Safavide du XVIe au XVIIIe si&egrave;cle,&rdquo; in idem, ed., <em>L&rsquo;h&eacute;ritage timouride. Iran&ndash;Asie centrale&ndash;Inde, XVe&ndash;XVIIIe si&egrave;cles, </em>Cahiers d&rsquo;Asie Centrale 3-4, 1997, pp. 313-31.</p>
<p>John E. Woods The <em>Aqquyunlu Clan, Confederation, Empire</em>, Minneapolis and Chicago, 1976.</p>


					<p>(Sholeh Quinn)</p>

